reviewText: Worth the time to watch. Not great but decent enough.
geat movie, had a surprising ending.
This is a human story and thats what I'm attracted to.

I thought this was a really interesting  movie.  Right from the beginning I thought, Uh oh, don't try to help someone seriously disturbed through friendship.  It became more complicated than that.  The acting was great, and I am a Schygulla fan.  I thought this showed her at her best.  Margaretha von Trotta is such a sensitive director, especially about women's issues.  The ending left me gasping.  I highly recommend it.
Complex, repressed characters in twisted relationships with a strange turn at the end.
It was OK. Moved a bit slow for me but the acting was good.
Not what I expected at all.
Interesting plot and some decent acting but very European and somewhat anit-climatic although the culmination was surprising.  But not a lesbian love story, at all.
